rComments: One of the kindest people I have ever met, he has a sarcastic sense of humor in class but if you ever talk to him in office hours you get the sense that he really does want everyone to succeed and do the best they can in his course. Too bad he's retiring.

good prof, helpful during office hours..but students hav to realize its a hard course, only way to do well is to do tones of problems and keep up...and have to realize there are multiple ways of gettin to the answer...so dont always be stressing about using the profs way...lab marking was ok...midterm was easy..and exam was a bit tough

What you put in is what you get. If you don't like chemistry stay away from this class. Advice for incoming students: 1- NEVER miss a lecture 2-Go to office hours 3-Start the practice problems early 4-ENJOY It because he's the BEST PROF at UTM!!!!

One of the best "teachers" that you will ever come across. He has designed the course with a lot of thought-does not encourage memorization and regurgitation (one of the reasons why the class average is low). His "I hate my wife" jokes are hillarious! But people should know that he makes all that up - in fact he married his highschool sweet-heart.

he is always willing to help you, if you are willing do the your work. expalins things very well but the exam is a killer.. god knows where he gets the questions from.. definately not from text book or his lectures.. his tests/exams are brutal.. very few people do well in this class. I hated UTM after taking this course with georges..
HES AN AMAZING PROFESSOR..THE BEST YOU WILL COME ACROSS OF
What's the point of being nice and teaching well if you were going to fail us anways? What an idiot. I have no respect for people like him. If you're jealous of premeds just go kill yourself.

LOVED HIM AND HIS CLASS! Think of orgo as a game of chess, there can be many different pathways (moves) to get to the final destination (product). To tell you the truth, becuase his tests are so comprehensive, you only really do well if you click with organic chem, otherwise you'll have to do way too much studying. You'll never kno til you take it.

Georges is a good prof, but course is alot of work. I put in 1 hour a day mon-fri, and 2 hours/day sat and sun, while doing a full-course load. I ended up with an 84% in 2006 class, so it can be done. Do past test and exams, althogu he wont use same questions he uses same techniques and methods. Memorize all reactions and you will be fine.Good luck

He's ONe of the BEST profs i'v taken so far in UNI, funny, smart n mann full of jokes...n i mean it!!! he even lets us take pictures of him! ... during his lab time!!! But every1 else is correct too...it is too hard...but i suppose if u do ur work u shouldn't have any trouble...Have FUN n GOOD LUCK!

Okay I'm gonna be objective and not let my bombed final exam skew things: this guy is a very good instructor. He has a natural talent to teach and is also very enthusiastic about the subject matter. But be warned! his tests are extremely difficult. It is much easier to fail than it is to pass. Good luck!

Amazing professor, clear and precise but extremely hard marker. I studied chemistry the most but still ended up with a 60. His exam this year was by far the hardest (60% failed it)and he himself calls it a "masterpiece". So guys if you are considering this course, make sure you are the best of the best of the few natural chemistry students.
Amazing! when he gives warnings LISTEN to them. tests and exams are exactly as he says: NEVER SEEN BEFORE. but immense fun course, work your ass off and you'll see the results, very fair to everyone.
He's the sexiest thing I've ever laid eyes on!!! He's mastered the sexy painter look with his attire.  Awesome teacher, for some reason really loves poker.
he's real tricky on tests, and a bit disorganized...but a really good teacher - in office hrs especially
This is the worst course/prof combo known to man. When he threatens things, he means them. Failure is immenent
